mvi-ldc-AIN-Index-economic.def: Defined as the standard deviation of the difference between agricultural production and its 20-year trend
mvi-ldc-AIN-Index-economic.name: Instability of agricultural production
mvi-ldc-AIN-Index-economic.source: CDP Secretariat, based on agricultural production data from FAO, FAOSTAT

mvi-ldc-XCON-Index-economic.def: Provides information on the exposure to trade shocks resulting from a concentrated export structure. Measures the product concentration of a country's exports
mvi-ldc-XCON-Index-economic.name: Export concentration
mvi-ldc-XCON-Index-economic.source: United Nations Conference on Trade and Development (UNCTAD)

mvi-ldc-XIN-Index-economic.def: The standard deivation of the difference between the value of annual export earnings and its 20-year trend
mvi-ldc-XIN-Index-economic.name: Instability of exports of goods and services
mvi-ldc-XIN-Index-economic.source: CDP Secretariat, based on data for exports and imports and goods and services and trade dependency (ratio of exports plus imports to GDP) from United Nations Statistics Division National Accounts Main Aggregates Database (AMA)
